source ? { source } : {}),\r\n\t\t\t\tstartedAt: Between<Date>(start as Date, end as Date),\r\n\t\t\t\tstoppedAt: Not(IsNull()),\r\n\t\t\t\temployeeId,\r\n\t\t\t\ttenantId,\r\n\t\t\t\torganizationId,\r\n\t\t\t\tisActive: true,\r\n\t\t\t\tisArchived: false\r\n\t\t\t},\r\n\t\t\torder: {\r\n\t\t\t\tstartedAt: 'DESC',\r\n\t\t\t\tcreatedAt: 'DESC',\r\n\t\t\t},\r\n\t\t\t...(request['relations'] ? { relations: request['relations'], } : {}),\r\n\t\t});\r\n```\r\nWe can optimize those with Query Builder. \r\n\r\nThis may also prevent some issues described in the:\r\n\r\n- https://github.com/typeorm/typeorm/issues/4738\r\n- https://github.com/typeorm/typeorm/issues/9139#issuecomment-1600538796\r\n- https://github.com/typeorm/typeorm/issues/10481\r\n- https://github.com/typeorm/typeorm/issues/3857\r\n- and so on\r\n\r\nNote: I think we do not use `relationLoadStrategy: query` anymore in our codebase but some of the issues above still happen under very heavy load with PostgreSQL and we have to optimize.\r\n\r\nFinally, we should also add more relevant indexes for each of those complex queries!","status":"open","priority":null,"size":null,"issueType":null,"estimate":null,"dueDate":"2024-02-24T18:30:48.794Z","public":true,"startDate":null,"resolvedAt":null,"version":null,"parentId":null,"projectId":"2337e147-1211-422d-b1b4-2750d70639d4","creatorId":"ed55e951-e773-4192-95e5-ce4d05dbea26","organizationSprintId":null,"taskStatusId":null,"taskSizeId":null,"taskPriorityId":null,"project":{"id":"2337e147-1211-422d-b1b4-2750d70639d4","createdAt":"2024-01-11T06:28:19.000Z","updatedAt":"2024-01-11T06:28:19.000Z","deletedAt":null,"isActive":true,"isArchived":false,"tenantId":"590b7eea-f690-4cfc-b29f-736c5c49c4f1","organizationId":"8060062b-6156-44ba-be78-d8685f0232af","name":"Gauzy Platform DevOps","startDate":null,"endDate":null,"billing":null,"currency":null,"public":null,"owner":null,"taskListType":"GRID","code":null,"description":null,"color":null,"billable":null,"billingFlat":null,"op